    • Field Detail

      • END_TIME_NOT_APPLICABLE

        public static final double END_TIME_NOT_APPLICABLE
        ID value for the end time of an event when that event has no end time defined.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • time

        public double time
        Holds the time of the event as a Julian day in TT. In case the event has a start and end times, set here the start time.

      • endTime

        public double endTime
        Holds the time of the end of an event as a Julian day in TT. Only set for certain events, like those for natural satellites.

      • eventType

        public SimpleEventElement.EVENT eventType
        Event id code. Constants defined in this class.

      • details

        public java.lang.String details
        Holds details on the event.

      • eventLocation

        public LocationElement eventLocation
        The equatorial position where this event occurs. Null by default, but can be used manually to set this information. For certain events it is set, like variable stars (position of the star), occultations and conjunctions.

      • body

        public java.lang.String body
        The name of the body that produces the event.

      • secondaryBody

        public java.lang.String secondaryBody
        The name of the secondary body that produces the event in case there are two. This occurs with eclipses of natural satellites, where the body is the satellite and the secondary body is the mother planet. For mutual events the secondary body is the body behind the primary one.

      • EVENTS

        public static final java.lang.String[] EVENTS
        The events as strings.

      • getElevation

        public double getElevation(ObserverElement obs,
                  EphemerisElement eph)
                    throws JPARSECException
        Returns the elevation of the event body above horizon for a given observer. Elevation is calculated respect the time of the maximum of the event (mean time between start and end) or respect to the start time in case end time is not known or not applicable.
        Parameters:
        obs - Observer object.
        eph - Ephemeris object.
        Returns:
        The elevation in radians, or -1 in case cannot be calculated.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.
